{"id":1266166355,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"7 months, 2 weeks","timestamp":1716500628,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1266166355/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"44.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n\n    public int getVal(char c){\n            if(c== 'I'){\n                return 1;\n            }else if (c== 'V'){\n                return 5;\n            }else if (c== 'X'){\n                return 10;\n            }else if (c== 'L'){\n                return 50;\n            }else if (c== 'C'){\n                return 100;\n            }else if (c== 'D'){\n                return 500;\n            }else if (c== 'M')\n                return 1000;\n            else\n                return 0;\n\n        }\n\n\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        int sum = 0;\n        int smallSum=0;\n\n        \n\n\n        for(int i =0; i<s.length(); i++){\n            smallSum +=getVal(s.charAt(i));\n\n            if(i<s.length()-1){\n                if(getVal(s.charAt(i))< getVal(s.charAt(i+1))){\n                    sum+= getVal(s.charAt(i+1)) - smallSum;\n                    smallSum= 0;\n                    i++;\n        \n                }else if (getVal(s.charAt(i))> getVal(s.charAt(i+1))){\n                    sum += smallSum;\n                    smallSum =0;\n                }\n\n            \n            }\n\n\n        }\n        sum+=smallSum;\n        return sum;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
